|cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Have you worked out how Romex achieves the seemingly impossible yet?  No?  Ok, I'll put you out of your misery: Romex achieves this by not permitting you to make a short-suit trial bid DIRECTLY.

You have to ask PERMISSION first and you do this by relaying in the next bid up over the agreed Major.

Thus   1@H - 2@H - 2@S   
and     1@S - 2@S - 2NT   are ASKING PERMISSION to make a short-suit trial bid rather than actually making one.

The idea here is that if you make this request, and partner is minimum or maximum they do not allow you to actually make the short-suit trial bid but instead sign off directly in 3 or 4 of the agreed Major, as appropriate.

The trick is that they only permit you to MAKE the short suit trial bid when they are mid-range AND it matters to THEM where your shortage is.
