cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  One thing that it's VERY important to be clear on concerning the whole issue of making Trial Bids is the Captaincy of the Hand.Once you make a trial bid (or ask permission to make one), you hand over the Captaincy of the Hand to PARTNER, 100%.    So if the bidding starts :@-
^c@21@H - 1@S
2@S - 3@D(Long Trial Bid for @S)
3@S(Not interested) - ???
^b@2If Responder now bids 4@S, ignoring Opener's statement with 3@S that they are not interested in game, this is unilaterally grabbing back the Captaincy of the Hand when the 3@D Trial Bid hands it over to Opener 100%. 

This is utterly wrong, tends to destroy partnership confidence in each other and is effectively saying "I know better than you, and what you think doesn't matter".

If you're not interested in hearing the answer to the question, then don't ask the question in the first place (ie: bid 4@S over 2@S in this instance).

